    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors accepted at Gradation 1 per MRL 2 scoping. CFD model is judged fit for purpose to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device, supporting the RH < 1 regulatory submission. The team noted informally that validation experiments were conducted exclusively at 22°C and 1 atm; the sensitivity of predicted RH to the broader clinical ambient temperature range (18–28°C), high-altitude pressure conditions (~0.85 atm), and electromagnetic interference from surgical suite equipment was not formally characterised. This environmental gap was discussed but not escalated to a formal weakener, and the package was accepted on the basis that the nominal laboratory conditions are representative of the majority of clinical use scenarios.",
